Key Match Events: England won by 5 wickets with 6 balls remaining
Sam Curran was named Player of the Match for his 3/12 performance
Ben Stokes scored an unbeaten 52 off 49 balls
Shan Masood had a concussion test after being hit on the helmet by Chris Jordan's delivery
Post-Match Reflections: Sam Curran was also named Player of the Series
England won the 2022/23 ICC Men's T20 World Cup
Miscellaneous Highlights: Match was held at Melbourne Cricket Ground
England elected to field first after winning the toss
